Myth: ### The Saharan Veil of Dune Dictum

In the blistering wastes of sun-scorched Saharath, where sandstorms flayed skin and mirages lured to thirst-madness, a grit-veiled nomad staggered at well-guard Sira's adobe burrow. Heat-haze warped his silhouette, his dune-orb shimmering illusory—parched pilgrim or silica-specter? Sira, tormented by droughts, her cisterns cracked and final date withering, shuddered. Scorpion swarms thirsted; sharing water and shade invited desiccation, her husk for jackals.

