Wastes howled. The nomad billowed, gales enthroning Sahar, sultan of eternal thirsts! "Guest-right is no evaporating dream, but arid axiom—ritual etched in erg's embrace, taboo of the entombing drift!" Zolt petrified to sandstone statue, scoured forever. Sira's wells gushed oases, bloodline dune-dominions.

Saharathans murmur: Hospitality is sand's summons; defy it, and the desert devours inexorably.

